TEND
  Transfer a commodity directly between two ships in the same sector.

SYNTAX
  tend <commodity> <tender-spec> <amount> <target-spec>

DESCRIPTION
  Moves goods straight from one ship's hold to another's, with no
  harbor and no sector ownership required.  This is how you get oil
  off an oil derrick parked in open ocean: the derrick can't unload
  onto owned land (there isn't any out there), and 'load'/'unload'
  only work at a harbor you own — 'tend' works ship-to-ship anywhere,
  as long as both ships are in the same sector.

  <commodity>    - single letter: o=oil f=food c=civ m=mil l=lcm etc.
  <tender-spec>  - ship uid, range (0-5), comma list, *, ~ (unassigned
                   ships), or a fleet letter (see 'info fleetadd') —
                   the ship(s) you're commanding to give or take cargo
  <amount>       - positive: move FROM tender TO target
                   negative: move FROM target TO tender (tender pulls in)
  <target-spec>  - same forms as <tender-spec> — the other ship(s) in
                   the deal

  Both ships must be in the same sector.  You must own the tender.
  The target must be yours too, or owned by a nation you're on
  Friendly terms with or better (see 'info relations').

  Cargo capacity is enforced per ship type — e.g. an oil exploration
  boat can only ever hold 1 oil (it's a scout, not a hauler), while
  an oil derrick holds 990 and a tanker holds 990.  Transfers are
  silently capped at whatever the receiving ship has room for.

EXAMPLE
  tend oil 1 500 5          move up to 500 oil from ship 1 to ship 5
  tend oil 1 -500 5         pull up to 500 oil from ship 5 onto ship 1
  tend food 0 999 1-4       spread ship 0's food across ships 1 through 4

WORKFLOW: KEEPING AN OIL RIG PARKED ON A RICH SPOT
  1. Sail an oil exploration boat around checking 'v' during navigate
     to find a sea sector with high oil content (see 'info navigate').
  2. Send an oil derrick there and leave it — it drills passively
     every update as long as it stays put and isn't 'off'.
  3. Periodically sail a tanker out to the same sector and run
     'tend oil <derrick> <amount> <tanker>' to pull the oil off.
  4. Sail the tanker back to a harbor and 'unload' it there.
  The derrick never has to leave the good spot, so it never wastes
  an update's production sailing back and forth.

